# Neo4j operator design terminology

When editing files under `design/`:

## API vocabulary (V1)

- **Primary** = `topology.primaries` (quorum / writers)
- **Secondary** = `topology.secondaries` with fixed keys **`analytics`** | **`read`**
- Do **not** use: `cores`, `replicaPools`, `serverRole`, `ReadReplica` as spec fields

## CRD model

- **One** workload CRD `Neo4j` (BDR-001) — embedded sections, not separate infra CRDs
- **Plugins**: assignment on pools + `pluginDefinitions` (BDR-004 Option E)
- **Backup/restore**: separate CRDs (different lifecycle)

## Decision records

- **BDR** = business (`design/decision-records/business/`)
- **ADR** = architecture (`design/decision-records/architecture/`)
- BDR-001/002/004 are **exemplars** — validate via `helm-semantic-concern-mapper`; amend/supersede when Helm code + Neo4j docs warrant it
- Read accepted BDRs before proposing CRD shape changes

## Helm analysis outputs

- Traceability via `design/analysis/helm-fields/_index.csv`
- Do not contradict accepted BDRs without marking `supersedes` or new BDR
